    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Here is a standard example of the list of `<script>` tags that would make sense:\n- `lodash`\n- `hogan`\n- `react`\n- `jquery`\n- `algoliasearch.jquery`\n- `algoliasearch-helper`\n- `autocomplete.jquery`\n- `instantsearch`\n\nI really think that creating bundles for each use case will become an unmaintanable mess, since we're just doing it for front-end implems where the dependencies have always been declared in sequence, and it isn't shocking.\n\nSome users might already have `jquery`, `lodash`, or `hogan` and ok, `hogan` is nothing, but `jquery` or `lodash` are big. Sometimes, you need the JS client in addition to `instantsearch`. \n\nMoreover, it will really be needed as soon as we'll have people building _widgets_, because they might want to use lodash or hogan or whatever, and we shouldn't have each widget built with its dependency if not needed.\n\nOn Shopify, it's really only about `jQuery`, and maybe lodash in some themes.\n",
